  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want to receive as many PNs (or one meaningful PN) as many messages i missed while being out of internet connection\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: As a user i want to understand clearly how many messages and events i missed while i  was being offline and my status app was running on background (for ex while i was in subway). Now when i reproduce such situtation i receive only 1 PN no matter how many events i missed\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nI want to receive either equal number of PNs with respect of messages i missed while being offline or I can receive 1 PN saying something like `you have 50 messages in 4 chats` (like Viber does)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n1 PN is shown no matter how many messages were sent to user\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- install status on device A (android)\r\n- install status on device B (ios)\r\n- add each other to contacts\r\n- as device B (ios) go on background and turn off any internet connection\r\n- as device A (android) send several messages to device B (ios) while device B is offline\r\n- as device A (android) kill status app\r\n- wait for several minutes\r\n- as device B (ios) turn on internet connection\r\n- as device B (ios) pay attention to the push notifications received\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: develop\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
